The article discusses President Obama's efforts to make college education more affordable and to ease the burden of student debt for millions of Americans. The President participated in a live question and answer session with Tumblr to address the issue and announced new executive actions to help alleviate the problem. The White House's Council of Economic Advisers and Domestic Policy Council also released a report highlighting the impact of student debt on young Americans and the economy. The report also includes data on how borrowers in each state would benefit from the President's actions and the Senate Democrats' bill.